# todorepl interactive agent configuration.
#
# Copy to .env (or export these in your shell) to configure the model the
# no-argument `todorepl` agent uses. Your todo database always stays on this
# machine; with the default local model nothing leaves it at all. A remote model
# only receives the conversation (your messages + the todos the agent reads) for
# inference — never the database.
#
# Every setting below is OPTIONAL and shown with its built-in default. With nothing
# set, todorepl uses a local Ollama model. Uncomment only what you change — leaving
# a stale value set (e.g. a local TODOREPL_BASE_URL) can misroute a cloud provider
# you switch to later.

# Provider: ollama | openai-compatible | anthropic | openai | gateway
# TODOREPL_PROVIDER=ollama

# Model id. Defaults to "llama3.1" for the local providers; required for cloud.
# TODOREPL_MODEL=llama3.1

# Base URL for the ollama / openai-compatible providers only.
# TODOREPL_BASE_URL=http://localhost:11434/v1

# API key. Ignored by local Ollama. For cloud providers set this, or use the
# provider-standard ANTHROPIC_API_KEY / OPENAI_API_KEY / AI_GATEWAY_API_KEY.
# TODOREPL_API_KEY=

# --- Example: hosted Anthropic model (sends the conversation to Anthropic; DB stays local) ---
# TODOREPL_PROVIDER=anthropic
# TODOREPL_MODEL=claude-sonnet-4-5
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...

# --- Example: Vercel AI Gateway (one key, many providers; sends the conversation, not your DB) ---
# Model ids are namespaced as "<provider>/<model>", e.g. anthropic/claude-sonnet-4.6
# or openai/gpt-4o. When deployed on Vercel, a VERCEL_OIDC_TOKEN is used automatically.
# TODOREPL_PROVIDER=gateway
# TODOREPL_MODEL=anthropic/claude-sonnet-4.6
# AI_GATEWAY_API_KEY=...
